DESCRIPTION
The goal of this project is to characterize the dynamics and electrostatics of the entire influenza viral envelope, comprised of 
neuraminidase (NA), hemagglutinin (HA), and M2-channel proteins embedded in a physiologically relevant lipid bilayer. 
This project will advance the state of the art in our understanding of influenza virulence, drug resistance, anti-viral 
therapeutic development, and pathogen-host interactions.
